name: Mount Moosilauke

current_conditions.ai_summary: The 'Gentle Giant' provides expansive views from its grassy summit. A favorite first 4,000-footer for many.

generated_description:
The Experience

Mount Moosilauke stands guard at the western edge of the White Mountains. Its broad, alpine meadow summit offers a unique perspective, looking east toward the rest of the range and west into Vermont.

The Challenge

While still a serious mountain, the Gorge Brook trail is considered one of the more moderate approaches to a 4,000-footer. The grade is consistent and well-maintained.

Local Insight

The Ravine Lodge at the base serves excellent food and offers a rustic, collegiate atmosphere.

trails_config.name: Gorge Brook and Carriage Loop
trails_config.description: The 'Gentle Giant' of the Whites. Offers a treeless summit with views stretching to the Green Mountains of Vermont.
trails_config.parking_info: Moosilauke Ravine Lodge, Ravine Rd, Benton, NH
